I"É<p><strong>Sealed classes</strong> in Kotlin are another new concept which was not there in Java. As the name suggests, sealed classes are closed and making them restricted or bounded class hierarchies.</p>

<p>Restricted means, we have specific number of sub classes similar to Enum. But the major difference between Enum and Sealed classes are in the enum we only have one instance per type whereas sealed classes can have multiple instances of the same class.</p>

<p>Sealed classes ensure type-safety by restricting the types to be matched at compile-time rather than at runtime.</p>

<hr />
<p>Declaration of Sealed Class:</p>

<p>To define a sealed class, just precede the class modifier with the sealed keyword.</p>

<p><code class="highlighter-rouge">sealed class Demo</code></p>

<blockquote>
  <p>The sealed classes also have one another distinct feature, their constructors are private by default.</p>
</blockquote>

<hr />

<p>A sealed class is implicitly abstract and hence it cannot be instantiated.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
